('w_environment_A1_01','tree','/triː/','noun','나무','A tall plant with a trunk and branches.','We planted a {tree} in the garden.','우리는 정원에 나무를 심었어요.','tree','A1','environment',1,'tree nature green forest park'),
('w_environment_A1_02','water','/ˈwɔːtər/','noun','물','A clear liquid that rivers, lakes, and the sea are made of.','Please don''t waste {water}.','물을 낭비하지 마세요.','water','A1','environment',1,'water river lake clean blue'),
('w_environment_A1_03','air','/ɛr/','noun','공기','The mixture of gases that surrounds the Earth.','Fresh {air} is good for your health.','신선한 공기는 건강에 좋아요.','air','A1','environment',1,'air sky wind fresh outdoors'),
('w_environment_A1_04','clean','/kliːn/','adjective','깨끗한','Free from dirt or harmful substances.','We need {clean} water to live.','우리는 살기 위해 깨끗한 물이 필요해요.','clean','A1','environment',1,'clean water pure clear nature'),
('w_environment_A1_05','nature','/ˈneɪtʃər/','noun','자연','The physical world including plants, animals, and the landscape.','I love going for walks in {nature}.','저는 자연 속에서 산책하는 걸 좋아해요.','nature','A1','environment',1,'nature landscape forest mountain scenery'),
('w_environment_A1_06','sun','/sʌn/','noun','태양','The star at the center of our solar system that gives light and heat.','The {sun} gives us light and warmth.','태양은 우리에게 빛과 따뜻함을 줘요.','sun','A1','environment',1,'sun sunshine sky bright warm'),
('w_environment_A1_07','earth','/ɜːrθ/','noun','지구','The planet on which we live.','We must take care of our {earth}.','우리는 지구를 돌봐야 해요.','earth','A1','environment',1,'earth planet globe world space'),
('w_environment_A1_08','green','/ɡriːn/','adjective','초록색의','The colour of grass and leaves; relating to environmental protection.','Let''s keep our city {green}.','우리 도시를 초록색으로 유지해요.','green','A1','environment',1,'green park grass plants nature'),
('w_environment_A1_09','plant','/plænt/','noun','식물','A living thing that grows in soil and uses sunlight for energy.','Every {plant} needs sunlight and water.','모든 식물은 햇빛과 물이 필요해요.','plant','A1','environment',1,'plant flower garden growth green'),
('w_environment_A1_10','animal','/ˈænɪməl/','noun','동물','A living creature that can move and breathe.','Every {animal} has a role in nature.','모든 동물은 자연에서 역할을 맡고 있어요.','animal','A1','environment',1,'animal wildlife nature habitat wild'),
('w_environment_A1_11','flower','/ˈflaʊər/','noun','꽃','The colorful part of a plant that attracts insects.','The {flower} bloomed in the spring.','꽃이 봄에 피었어요.','flower','A1','environment',1,'flower bloom garden colorful spring'),
('w_environment_A1_12','sky','/skaɪ/','noun','하늘','The space above the earth that you see when you look up.','The {sky} was clear and blue today.','오늘 하늘이 맑고 파랬어요.','sky','A1','environment',1,'sky blue cloud sunshine weather'),
('w_environment_A1_13','rain','/reɪn/','noun','비','Water that falls from clouds in small drops.','The {rain} waters the plants.','비가 식물에게 물을 줘요.','rain','A1','environment',1,'rain water cloud weather nature'),
('w_environment_A1_14','snow','/snoʊ/','noun','눈','Small white pieces of frozen water that fall from the sky.','Children love to play in the {snow}.','아이들은 눈 속에서 노는 걸 좋아해요.','snow','A1','environment',1,'snow winter white cold ice'),
('w_environment_A1_15','rock','/rɒk/','noun','바위','A solid piece of stone.','We sat on a big {rock} by the river.','우리는 강가 큰 바위에 앉았어요.','rock','A1','environment',1,'rock stone mountain nature outdoor'),
('w_environment_A1_16','sea','/siː/','noun','바다','The large area of salt water that covers most of the Earth.','The {sea} is home to many creatures.','바다는 많은 생물의 보금자리예요.','sea','A1','environment',1,'sea ocean water wave blue'),
('w_environment_A1_17','fish','/fɪʃ/','noun','물고기','A creature that lives in water and breathes through gills.','There are many {fish} in the river.','강에 물고기가 많아요.','fish','A1','environment',1,'fish ocean water marine nature'),
('w_environment_A1_18','bird','/bɜːrd/','noun','새','A creature with wings and feathers that can usually fly.','The {bird} sings every morning.','새는 매일 아침 노래해요.','bird','A1','environment',1,'bird wing sky feather nature'),
('w_environment_A1_19','leaf','/liːf/','noun','나뭇잎','The flat, green part of a plant that grows from a stem or branch.','A {leaf} fell from the tree.','나뭇잎 하나가 나무에서 떨어졌어요.','leaf','A1','environment',1,'leaf tree green autumn nature'),
('w_environment_A1_20','grass','/ɡræs/','noun','풀','The short green plant that covers the ground in fields and gardens.','The {grass} is soft under your feet.','풀이 발 아래에서 부드러워요.','grass','A1','environment',1,'grass green field meadow nature'),
('w_environment_A1_21','wind','/wɪnd/','noun','바람','The natural movement of air.','The {wind} blew the leaves away.','바람이 나뭇잎들을 날려버렸어요.','wind','A1','environment',1,'wind breeze nature outdoors air'),
('w_environment_A1_22','fire','/faɪər/','noun','불','The heat, light, and flames produced when something burns.','{Fire} can destroy a whole forest.','불은 숲 전체를 태울 수 있어요.','fire','A1','environment',1,'fire flame heat danger forest'),
('w_environment_A1_23','sand','/sænd/','noun','모래','Tiny pieces of rock found on beaches and in deserts.','The {sand} was warm on the beach.','해변의 모래가 따뜻했어요.','sand','A1','environment',1,'sand beach desert warm nature'),
('w_environment_A1_24','lake','/leɪk/','noun','호수','A large area of water surrounded by land.','We went swimming in the {lake}.','우리는 호수에서 수영했어요.','lake','A1','environment',1,'lake water nature reflection mountain'),
('w_environment_A1_25','mountain','/ˈmaʊntɪn/','noun','산','A large, high piece of land with steep sides.','The {mountain} was covered in snow.','산이 눈으로 덮여 있었어요.','mountain','A1','environment',1,'mountain peak snow landscape nature'),
('w_environment_A1_26','cloud','/klaʊd/','noun','구름','A white or grey mass of water vapour in the sky.','A dark {cloud} covered the sun.','검은 구름이 태양을 가렸어요.','cloud','A1','environment',1,'cloud sky weather white grey'),
('w_environment_A1_27','light','/laɪt/','noun','빛','The energy that makes things visible.','Sunlight is natural {light}.','햇빛은 자연 빛이에요.','light','A1','environment',1,'light sunlight bright nature energy'),
('w_environment_A1_28','dark','/dɑːrk/','adjective','어두운','With very little or no light.','It gets {dark} early in winter.','겨울에는 일찍 어두워져요.','dark','A1','environment',1,'dark night sky shadow nature'),
('w_environment_A1_29','hot','/hɒt/','adjective','더운','Having a high temperature.','It is very {hot} in summer.','여름에는 매우 더워요.','hot','A1','environment',1,'hot sun desert summer heat'),
('w_environment_A1_30','cold','/koʊld/','adjective','추운','Having a low temperature.','The water is very {cold} in winter.','겨울에는 물이 매우 차가워요.','cold','A1','environment',1,'cold winter ice snow frost'),
('w_environment_A1_31','ground','/ɡraʊnd/','noun','땅','The solid surface of the Earth.','Seeds grow under the {ground}.','씨앗은 땅 속에서 자라요.','ground','A1','environment',1,'ground soil earth nature field'),
('w_environment_A1_32','river','/ˈrɪvər/','noun','강','A large stream of water that flows to the sea.','We had a picnic by the {river}.','우리는 강가에서 소풍을 즐겼어요.','river','A1','environment',1,'river water stream nature landscape'),
('w_environment_A1_33','forest','/ˈfɔːrɪst/','noun','숲','A large area of land covered with trees.','The {forest} is full of wildlife.','숲에는 야생동물이 가득해요.','forest','A1','environment',1,'forest trees green nature wild'),
('w_environment_A1_34','soil','/sɔɪl/','noun','흙','The top layer of the earth in which plants grow.','Plants need healthy {soil} to grow.','식물이 자라려면 건강한 흙이 필요해요.','soil','A1','environment',1,'soil earth garden plant nature'),
('w_environment_A1_35','wet','/wɛt/','adjective','젖은','Covered with or containing liquid, especially water.','The {wet} ground smells fresh after rain.','비가 온 후 젖은 땅에서 신선한 냄새가 나요.','wet','A1','environment',1,'wet rain water puddle nature'),

