('w_environment_A2_01','recycle','/ˌriːˈsaɪkəl/','verb','재활용하다','To process used materials so they can be used again.','We should {recycle} our bottles and cans.','우리는 병과 캔을 재활용해야 해요.','recycle','A2','environment',1,'recycle bin waste green eco'),
('w_environment_A2_02','pollution','/pəˈluːʃən/','noun','오염','The presence of harmful substances in the environment.','Air {pollution} is bad for our lungs.','대기 오염은 폐에 나빠요.','pollution','A2','environment',1,'pollution smog city factory smoke'),
('w_environment_A2_03','energy','/ˈɛnərdʒi/','noun','에너지','The power from sources such as electricity or fuel.','We should save {energy} at home.','우리는 집에서 에너지를 아껴야 해요.','energy','A2','environment',1,'energy power electricity solar wind'),
('w_environment_A2_04','waste','/weɪst/','noun','쓰레기, 낭비','Materials that are no longer needed and thrown away.','Try not to create too much {waste}.','쓰레기를 너무 많이 만들지 않으려고 노력해요.','waste','A2','environment',1,'waste trash bin rubbish recycle'),
