('w_environment_A2_23','public transport','/ˈpʌblɪk ˈtrænspɔːrt/','noun','대중교통','Buses, trains, and other vehicles available to the public.','Use {public transport} to reduce pollution.','오염을 줄이기 위해 대중교통을 이용해요.','public transport','A2','environment',1,'public transport bus train green city'),
('w_environment_A2_24','beach','/biːtʃ/','noun','해변','An area of sand or small stones near the sea.','We cleaned up the {beach} last Sunday.','지난 일요일에 해변을 청소했어요.','beach','A2','environment',1,'beach clean ocean sand nature'),
('w_environment_A2_25','wildlife','/ˈwaɪldlaɪf/','noun','야생동물','Animals and plants living in their natural environment.','We must protect local {wildlife}.','지역 야생동물을 보호해야 해요.','wildlife','A2','environment',1,'wildlife animal nature habitat wild'),
('w_environment_A2_26','rubbish','/ˈrʌbɪʃ/','noun','쓰레기','Unwanted material or waste.','There is too much {rubbish} on the streets.','거리에 쓰레기가 너무 많아요.','rubbish','A2','environment',1,'rubbish trash bin waste street'),
('w_environment_A2_27','compost','/ˈkɒmpɒst/','noun','퇴비','Decayed plant and food waste used to improve soil.','I add food scraps to the {compost} bin.','음식물 쓰레기를 퇴비통에 넣어요.','compost','A2','environment',1,'compost soil garden organic eco'),
('w_environment_A2_28','flood','/flʌd/','noun','홍수','A large amount of water covering an area that is usually dry.','The {flood} damaged many homes.','홍수로 많은 집이 피해를 입었어요.','flood','A2','environment',1,'flood water disaster rain nature'),
('w_environment_A2_29','storm','/stɔːrm/','noun','폭풍','Severe weather with heavy rain, strong winds, and often thunder.','A big {storm} hit the coast last night.','어젯밤 해안에 큰 폭풍이 몰아쳤어요.','storm','A2','environment',1,'storm rain wind thunder weather'),
('w_environment_A2_30','temperature','/ˈtɛmprɪtʃər/','noun','온도','A measure of how hot or cold something is.','The {temperature} is rising every year.','온도가 매년 오르고 있어요.','temperature','A2','environment',1,'temperature thermometer heat climate global'),
('w_environment_A2_31','fresh','/frɛʃ/','adjective','신선한','Not containing harmful substances; clean and pure.','We need {fresh} air and clean water.','신선한 공기와 깨끗한 물이 필요해요.','fresh','A2','environment',1,'fresh air water clean nature green'),
('w_environment_A2_32','drought','/draʊt/','noun','가뭄','A long period with no rain.','The {drought} dried up the river completely.','가뭄으로 강이 완전히 말라버렸어요.','drought','A2','environment',1,'drought dry land cracked desert'),
('w_environment_A2_33','ocean','/ˈoʊʃən/','noun','해양','The large area of salt water covering most of the earth.','The {ocean} absorbs a lot of carbon dioxide.','해양은 이산화탄소를 많이 흡수해요.','ocean','A2','environment',1,'ocean sea water blue marine'),
('w_environment_A2_34','environment','/ɪnˈvaɪrənmənt/','noun','환경','The natural world in which people, animals, and plants live.','We must care for the {environment}.','우리는 환경을 돌봐야 해요.','environment','A2','environment',1,'environment nature earth green eco'),
('w_environment_A2_35','fuel','/fjuːəl/','noun','연료','A material that produces heat or energy when burned.','Cars burn {fuel} and release gases.','자동차는 연료를 태워 가스를 배출해요.','fuel','A2','environment',1,'fuel gas petrol car energy'),

