('w_environment_B1_01','climate change','/ˈklaɪmɪt tʃeɪndʒ/','noun phrase','기후 변화','Long-term shifts in global temperatures and weather patterns.','Scientists warn that {climate change} is accelerating.','과학자들은 기후 변화가 가속화되고 있다고 경고해요.','climate change','B1','environment',1,'climate change globe heat weather map'),
('w_environment_B1_02','carbon','/ˈkɑːrbən/','noun','탄소','A chemical element that is found in all living things.','We need to cut our {carbon} emissions.','우리는 탄소 배출량을 줄여야 해요.','carbon','B1','environment',1,'carbon molecule element chemistry eco'),
('w_environment_B1_03','emission','/ɪˈmɪʃən/','noun','배출(량)','Gases or other substances released into the air.','Car {emissions} are a major source of pollution.','자동차 배출가스는 주요 오염원이에요.','emission','B1','environment',1,'emission exhaust gas factory smoke'),
('w_environment_B1_04','sustainable','/səˈsteɪnəbəl/','adjective','지속 가능한','Able to be maintained without harming the environment.','We need {sustainable} farming practices.','우리는 지속 가능한 농업 방식이 필요해요.','sustainable','B1','environment',1,'sustainable farm eco green agriculture'),
('w_environment_B1_05','renewable','/rɪˈnjuːəbəl/','adjective','재생 가능한','Coming from a source that will not run out.','Wind power is a {renewable} energy source.','풍력은 재생 가능한 에너지원이에요.','renewable','B1','environment',1,'renewable wind solar energy turbine'),
('w_environment_B1_06','ecosystem','/ˈiːkoʊsɪstəm/','noun','생태계','A community of living organisms and their environment.','The rainforest {ecosystem} is very complex.','열대우림 생태계는 매우 복잡해요.','ecosystem','B1','environment',1,'ecosystem forest wildlife nature complex'),
('w_environment_B1_07','biodiversity','/ˌbaɪoʊdaɪˈvɜːrsɪti/','noun','생물 다양성','The variety of plant and animal life in a habitat.','Protecting {biodiversity} is vital for ecosystems.','생물 다양성 보호는 생태계에 필수적이에요.','biodiversity','B1','environment',1,'biodiversity species animals plants rainforest'),
